>
  <h1>Things I Use</h1>
  <section id="web-development">
    <h2 id="web-development">Web Development</h2>
    <p>
      A 15-inch MacBook Air (Apple M2, 2023) does everything I need it to do
      with zero problems. My mouse is an <a
        href="https://www.logitech.com/en-us/products/mice/mx-master-3s-mac-bluetooth-mouse.910-006570.html?srsltid=AfmBOoo2Xc7jTQQ4c4zKe8gUs70L2M_3pkXTCLZSvoVpXCdnlWZQNmYi"
        >MX Master 3S for Mac</a
      >, which is pretty gentle on my fingers and wrists, but I still have a
      little soreness, so I wear some Walgreens compression gloves which help a
      ton.
    </p>
    <p>
      I code in VS Code. I use <a href="https://github.com/samfeldstein/">GitHub</a
      > for version control. I develop in <a
        href="https://www.google.com/chrome/">Google Chrome</a
      > and sometimes <a href="https://www.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/developer/"
        >Firefox Developer Edition</a
      >. I design in <a href="https://www.figma.com">Figma</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      I built this website with <a href="https://astro.build/">Astro</a>, and I
      built my <a href="https://notebook.samfeldstein.xyz/">notebook</a> with <a
        href="https://www.11ty.dev">Eleventy</a
      >.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="writing-and-reading">
    <h2 id="writing-and-reading">Writing and Reading</h2>
    <p>
      I write and takes <a href="https://notebook.samfeldstein.xyz/">notes</a> in
      <a href="https://obsidian.md/">Obsidian</a>. I use the Blue Topaz theme
      with the Style Settings, Hider, and Typewriter Scroll plugins.
    </p>

    <p>
      <a href="https://enso.sonnet.io/">Enso</a> comes in handy for distraction-free
      word-dumping. I&#39;d use <a href="https://www.beat-app.fi">beat</a> if I still
      wrote screenplays, except maybe not, because <a
        href="https://code.visualstudio.com/">VS Code</a
      > has a great <a
        href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=piersdeseilligny.betterfountain"
        >fountain plugin</a
      >.
    </p>
    <p>
      I track feeds and read articles with <a href="https://readwise.io/"
        >Readwise</a
      >. For books, I have a Kindle and a library card. <a
        href="https://www.overdrive.com/apps/libby">Libby</a
      > rules, as does the <a href="https://archive.org">Internet Archive</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      To annotate eBooks, I use Readwise. To annotate articles, I use either the <a
        href="https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/readwise-highlighter/jjhefcfhmnkfeepcpnilbbkaadhngkbi"
        >Readwise Highlighter extension</a
      > or the <a
        href="https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/obsidian-web-clipper/cnjifjpddelmedmihgijeibhnjfabmlf"
        >Obsidian Web Clipper extension</a
      >.
    </p>

    <p>
      All notes I take in <a href="https://read.readwise.io">Readwise Reader</a>
      (or its highlighter extension), on my Kindle, or in iBooks show up in my Readwise
      database, which I export to Google Drive and Obsidian. All notes I take with
      Obsidian Web Clipper show up in...Obsidian.
    </p>
    <p>
      I track books I&#39;ve read and want to read with <a
        href="https://www.librarything.com/home">LibraryThing</a
      >.
    </p>
    <p>
      I memorize information with <a href="https://apps.ankiweb.net/">Anki</a>.
    </p>
